Actually the point here is not that trojan "is equivalent to xxx". It is that the protocol gives v2ray the ability to control the redirection itself (instead of relying on nginx or other softwares) and gives you the freedom to redirect illegal connections to any service of your choice, like SMTP, IRC, and etc (not just those provided by nginx), and actually make use of them.
As the core author of trojan, I truly hope the protocol can be incorporated into v2ray..

